title: The Who - 1975-11-20 - Houston - Pro Shot 5.1 DVD9
description:

The Who - Summit '75 - 4 REEL Dual Layer Version
DVD9 Ripped with Mac The Ripper
I suggest getting a dual layer blank for this one, 6.93 GB, don't
squeeze it or you'll see a slightly degraded pic.

1. Summit '75 - complete
2. Pontiac '75 - picks up at Pinball Wizard
3. '72 Paris Outdoor Fest
4. '73 "Long Live Rock"- OGWT
5. '75 Keith Moon Interview
6. Roadie Film

Unquestionably the finest, complete live Who performance from the 70's.
It also includes about 60 minutes of Pontiac '75, a Paris '72 outdoor
festival clip, a '73 "Long Live Rock" clip, a '75 Interview with Keith
Moon, and a roadie film on the '72/'73? tours...
A fitting document of one of the world's best ever rock bands...while
they were still breaking new ground. Rare performances of Dreaming From
The Waist and How Ever Much I Booze and a good deal of Tommy with Moon
doing lead vocals on the odd bits...all members are in rare form in
this pristine recording, LONG LIVE ROCK !!!!
